For subspaces $U,V\subseteq\mathbb{R}^n$:
- the **intersection** $U\cap V=\{w:w\in U\text{ and }w\in V\}$ is a subspace (vectors in both);
- the **sum** $U+V=\{u+v:u\in U,\,v\in V\}$ is a subspace — the span of all vectors of $U$ together with all vectors of $V$. It is the smallest subspace containing both.
